`,e(l.p,{children:["The primary feature of statecharts is that states can be organized in a ",e(l.em,{children:"hierarchy"}),": A statechart is a ",e(l.a,{href:"https://statecharts.dev/what-is-a-state-machine.html",children:"state machine"})," where each state in the state machine may define its own ",e(l.em,{children:"subordinate"})," state machines, called ",e(l.em,{children:"substates"}),". Those states can again define substates."]}),`
